We may even get a KO at round 2 this time round .. Tyson can see the right hand before Wilder even thought of throwing the right hand.. so if he think he can catch Fury after 19 rounds of boxing and not fully clean catching him he is on pipe dream.. LOL

snippet.textDisplay: Wilder is a great player. But Fury outplayed him on THE DAY. That's what heavy weight boxing championship is all about. Now on your point about his legs. His legs were fine -- his sense of balance was NOT !  Human body balance is maintained by liquid in the eardrum which is used by balance sensors. Fury's punches burst open this system in early rounds. So wilder started to lose balance.  Off balanced it became increasingly difficult for him to fight against the mighty challenger Tyson Fury. And also his body was taking toll through great Jabs, Precise Powerful Body shots (They are extremely painful) and Body weight that Fury was putting on him at every clinch. Wilder's mouth was full of blood and eardrum was constantly bleeding too for about 15 mins before finally match was declared as TKO. His corner made the right decision. Wilder, otherwise would have died or would have suffered lifetime injuries that evening. Awesome fight and complete credit goes to Fury.. lets acknowledge is victory !!

snippet.textDisplay: Best day ever. The racebaiting, pathetic, rabid, UK-hating, delusional beyonce fans and trolls can disappear from the face of the Earth. Thank you Lord for exposing this fraud tonight!!!! The WBC belt was held hostage for waaaaay too long! And beyonce really believes she wud've beat and even ko'd a prime iron mike!!!!! Her team of yesmen were like 'Use the right hand D!' .... like a clueless deer in the headlights, LOL seriously that was their 'advice'!!! No adjustments, no idea what to do, no real useful advice, no actual boxing talk. I was surprised they didn't add 'remember move with your feet and punch using your fists D!' Deontay is garbage. He cannot box. The man has no balance or coordination, zero fundamentals and basics, no footwork, no defense, no idea of setting up shots or using the ring properly, no idea on how to read a fighter and make adjustments accordingly, no ring IQ whatsoever, no idea what feints or head movement are, no jab, no body shots, no idea on how to fight going backwards when actually pressured, no distance control and management or idea of timing / angles / appropriate punch selection, nothing besides a right hand, no hook, no uppercut, no combinations, NOTHING. Just a wild hailmary right hand which he somehow manages to time properly in spots. Surrounded by horrible yesmen and useless trainers .... just because Mark Breland was a successful amateur and good pro doesn't automatically mean he will make a great trainer. He isn't, he never developed deontay's skills because he thought the right hand would always bail him out, and partly also because Deontay can only do so much and probably didn't want to listen and a yesman will not open your eyes and push you to better yourself, only keep furthering and one upping your denial and ignorance. When you are naturally incompetent and inept at something, there is only so much you can do with it anyway. Breland and jay deas were always like 'deontay doesn't need to do this or that, just work with what he has' (just a right hand). Disgusting yesmen, rubbish coaching. This is what happens when you are hyped and you start believing your own hype! When you are full of yourself and do not humble yourself down a notch, and keep spreading negativity on other fighters. When you shit on legends like on arrogant prick like you did with Mike Tyson and others who paved the way for you, just for publicity. When you are never really tested. When you never listen to fans and trainers and boxing experts telling you that you must learn how to box and the right hand will not always bail you out. What happens when you are too full of yourself to make a career high paying fight with AJ because you really believe you can smash anyone with just a one trick pony style and the fight will still be there someday. This is karma for firing Lou DiBella for trying to set up a meeting with DAZN to make the AJ fight, and for shitting on AJ when he was down. (Let us see you come back now! Your 'performance' was 10x more pathetic than AJ's, he at least got a knockdown and won rounds and got up 4 times).  This is karma for ducking Dillian Whyte, Povetkin, Joseph Parker, Wladimir Klitschko and Joshua. And for cherrypicking Fury when he was at his weakest and still getting handed a lucky draw and not being a man about it, being in total denial and not admitting you should have lost that night and give him his props. Saying dumb shit like 'it's because the judges were smart and see through the bs'. This is what you get for still fighting binmen ever after you won the title, when you keep ducking good competition designed to slowly work your way up through solid tests, and when you do not listen to people telling you to learn good boxing fundamentals and skills and get trainers who aren't a bunch of yesmen who are in it for the money while the pot is still hot. You were fed over 40 binmen and the only half decent fighter you fought (who was 40yo at the time btw) almost killed you the first time and thoroughly gave you a boxing lesson the second time around before you knocked him out with your equaliser when he made a very dumb mistake. But no more. Learn how to box and make adjustments, and get good trainers not a bunch of yesmen .... or just gtfo of boxing once and for all .... I personally prefer the latter, FRAUD. Take your dumb annoying fangirls with you too.
